The paper discusses the training of support vector machines (SVMs) using optimization methods, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the Frank-Wolfe algorithm, which is commonly used in optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SVMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The paper also mentions the use of kernel functions, which is a common technique in data science (cs.DS) and neural networks (cs.NE).
